owlsurfing|Babu’s Best Friend 2024-04-14 2:45 AM
Story time!
2:49 AM
So when I was like 6-8 years old my mom decided that it would be a good idea to get chickens. The responsibility of feeding the chickens landed on us kids so my older brother, my older sister, myself, and my younger brother. We would go in pairs of one older and one younger who had “chicken chore” and occasionally we would forget to feed the chickens so they would get a wee bit hungry and start eating the eggs and such. Eventually it got to the point where they were super aggressive due to starvation. And because of their aggression none of us liked to feed them so there was that loop. Eventually stuff started getting to the chickens and they all died. Clucky (my chicken) had managed to survive the longest . So in short our chickens were super aggressive and would peck us. Traumatizing for a child of that age. (edited)
